Set over half a century before the birth of Harry Potter, Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them introduces fans to a new era of magic. After being expelled from Hogwarts, Newt Scamander travels to New York with a mysterious briefcase. Inside the briefcase, Newt has built a home for the most magnificent magical beasts. However, some of the beasts escape from the briefcase and unleash terror on the city. The film is based on a book by J.K Rowling (written under the Pseudonym Newt Scamander) and serves as Rowling&rsquo;s screen writing debut. Rating: 4 stars